Jon Reiter, a contractor from Kenwood, California, was attempting third ascent to the summit when avalanche hit .
At least 17 climbers, including three Americans, and many sherpas died in the avalanche .
Reiter managed to zip a dead body into a sleeping bag, but one doctor told him: 'Most of them are not going to survive'
He said: 'God definitely had his hand in my survival. My cold took me out of the danger zone'